SIMPLE: exile
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exile
<hw>Ex"ile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>exil</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>exilium</ets>, <ets>exsilium</ets>, fr. <ets>exsuil</ets>
one who quits, or is banished from, his native soil; <ets>ex</ets> out +
<ets>solum</ets> ground, land, soil, or perh. fr.the root of
<ets>salire</ets> to leap, spring; cf. F. <ets>exil</ets>. Cf.
<er>Sole</er> of the foot, <er>Saltation</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Forced separation from one's native country; expulsion from one's
home by the civil authority; banishment; sometimes, voluntary separation
from one's native country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let them be recalled from their <qex>exile</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The person expelled from his country by authority;
also, one who separates himself from his home.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou art in <qex>exile</qex>, and thou must not stay.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Banishment; proscription; expulsion.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Exile
<hw>Ex"ile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Exiled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Exiling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To banish or expel from one's own
country or home; to drive away.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Exiled</xex> from
eternal God.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Calling home our <qex>exiled</qex> friends abroad.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Banish</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Exile
<hw>Ex*ile"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exilis</ets>.]</ety> <def>Small; slender; thin; fine.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>exile</xex> sound.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exilement</ent>⟦br⟧
